04/10/2004
SLUNJ, Croatia -- A joint military exercise began on Saturday (2 October) in the Croatian town of Slunj. 
The two-week exercise, organised under the Adriatic Charter, involves forces from Croatia, Macedonia, Albania and the United States. 
The three Balkan countries are co-operating in their bids for NATO integration.
Also Saturday, in an interview with Jutarnji List, Croatian Ambassador to NATO Anton Tus acknowledged that his country would not be allowed to join NATO as long as fugitive General Ante Gotovina remains at large. 
Tus was in Brussels, presenting Croatia's third national plan for implementation of NATO integration obligations. 
(Jutarnji List - 03/10/04; HINA - 02/10/04)
